\textbf{Problem 1 (smoke -- trivial).} Prove that $1 + 1 = 2$ in the natural numbers $\mathbb{N}$, working from the Peano axioms. A two-paragraph proof is sufficient. The goal here is to exercise the shortest possible Author/Critic loop end-to-end; the mathematical content is intentionally minimal.
