\textbf{Problem 5 (smoke -- citation handling).} State and prove the Cantor--Bernstein--Schroeder theorem: if there exist injections $A \hookrightarrow B$ and $B \hookrightarrow A$, then $|A| = |B|$. Provide at least two genuine bibliographic references (with author, title, year, and either DOI or arXiv identifier) for the historical context and for an accessible modern exposition. The references should appear in a real \texttt{references.bib} entry and be cited via \texttt{$\backslash$cite} in the body of \texttt{answer.tex}.
\end{document}

